efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1)
space complexity: O(n)
explanation: Uses two stacks. The main stack stores all elements, and the minStack stores the minimum element encountered so far. When pushing, if the new element is less than or equal to the current minimum, it's pushed onto minStack. Popping removes from the main stack, and if the popped element is the current minimum, it's also removed from minStack.  This ensures constant time complexity for all operations. Space complexity is O(n) as we store all elements in the main stack.

